	🌟 INTERMEDIATE METHODS
	
	Intermediate operations always return a Stream and are lazy (they don’t run until a terminal op is used).
	
	1. filter()
	Keeps elements that match a condition.
	
	2. map()
	Transforms each element.
	
	3. flatMap()
	Flattens nested streams.
	
	4. sorted()
	Sorts elements (natural or custom comparator).
	
	5. distinct()
	Removes duplicates.
	
	6. limit()
	Limits the number of elements.
	
	7. skip()
	Skips first n elements.
	
	8. peek()
	Debugging — allows looking at elements without consuming them.
	
	9. mapToInt(), mapToLong(), mapToDouble()
	Converts object stream → primitive stream.
	
	10. flatMapToInt(), flatMapToLong(), flatMapToDouble()
	Flatten + convert to primitive stream.
	
	11. boxed()
	Converts primitive stream → object stream.
	
	🌟 TERMINAL METHODS
	
	Terminal operations produce a result (value, Optional, list, or side-effect) and end the stream.
	
	1. forEach()	
	Performs an action for each element.
	
	2. forEachOrdered()
	Same as forEach, but maintains encounter order.
	
	3. collect()	
	Collects result into List/Set/Map or custom collector.
	
	4. toArray()	
	Returns array of elements.
	
	5. reduce()	
	Reduces stream into a single value (sum, product, etc.).
	
	6. count()	
	Counts number of elements.
	
	7. findFirst()	
	Returns first element (Optional).
	
	8. findAny()	
	Returns any element (Optional) – usually for parallel streams.
	
	9. anyMatch()	
	Returns true if any element matches.
	
	10. allMatch()
	Returns true if all elements match.
	
	11. noneMatch()	
	True if no elements match.
	
	12. min()
	Finds minimum element.
	
	13. max()
	Finds maximum element.
	
	14. sum() (for IntStream/LongStream/DoubleStream)
	Adds all values.
	
	15. average()
	Returns the average (OptionalDouble).